      <h2>Gopher Gassers & Burrow Fumigation</h2>
      <p>When you’ve got a deep, branching tunnel network and traps aren’t producing — gassers are the move. I’ve used them when a gopher has gone dormant or when I’m dealing with a complex system where I can’t pinpoint the active run. The key is sealing every exit hole before you light one, or you’re just fumigating your lawn for nothing.</p>
      <p>For a full step-by-step on burrow fumigation, see the <a href="/methods/carbon-monoxide" style="color: #047857; font-weight: bold;">Carbon Monoxide Burrow Treatment guide</a>.</p>
